		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Just starting out...<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, May 21st 11:27 AM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=10535308744927&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=10535308744927&num=2&post=1&replyto=10535308744927"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class=sm href="/db/journal2.html?user=200538"><img src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=10535308744927></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=200538"><span id=>gladkost</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>17 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gladkost&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>So I am making a bard --I am excited because I have seen what a good bard can do and it seems like so much fun--plus my guild really needs a bard!&nbsp;&nbsp;But I am unsure of how to start--For example--Which stat is the most important when making a bard?  Is there one race that is better than another?  Are there any XP penalties depending on which race you choose?  Is the choice of deity important?  I plan on making this a high level character--Love the epic--still a great weapon even after Luclin--Any info that you can share would be great--Thanks<br><br>Zak</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Zaknafei<br><br>Forest Stalker</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, May 22nd 9:38 AM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=10535308744927&num=2&post=1&replyto=105360821627884"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=105360821627884></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=61546"><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>1262 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.66]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>So many questions and no easy answers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first thing to think about is how do you plan to play your bard?  Will the emphasis be on magic or melee or about an even split?  Personally, I tend to melee a lot but have been known to play the ghetto enchanter from time to time.<br><br>None of the races open for bards have any major experience penalties so don't concern yourself about that.<br><br>The main stats for a bard are DEX, CHA, STR, and (as with any class) STA.  DEX helps you learn melee skills faster and reduces the frequency of missed notes (the bard equivelent of a spell fizzle).  CHA helps with charm songs and also with reducing the chance a mob will aggro on you after a failed harmonize.  STR is needed since bards do get to wear plate armor and carry most melee weapons (no 2 handers but thats about it). STA affects the amount of HP you get and how fast you fatigue during combat, jumping, and swimming. INT plays a factor in the mid to high end games since a few of the bard songs actually do use mana. Don't lose sleep over it though.<br><br>Deity is not important unless you plan on wearing deity specific armors.  The downside of having a deity is that it will limit places you can travel to, even with illusions.  <br><br>Which race you choose doesn't really matter much with bards.  Humans can't see in the dark. That's about the only downside I can think of. Very easy to offset with simple gear. Bards are so versitile that the race factor just doesn't affect the class performance much at all.  Vah Shir are slightly better at melee due to the high starting STR.  Wood Elves are slightly better on the defensive skills.  Early on this makes some difference but in the high end game your gear and songs will more than make up for any minor deficiencies.  Go with what looks cool to you.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
